article.description: — Jalen Rucker scored 25 points and Matt Dove scored 14 and Army beat American 76-66 on Wednesday night for its fifth-straight win.
article.headline: Rucker scores 25 to lift Army past American 76-66
article.linkText: Rucker scores 25 to lift Army past American 76-66
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. -- — Jalen Rucker scored 25 points and Matt Dove scored 14 and Army beat American 76-66 on Wednesday night for its fifth-straight win. Chris Mann added 11 points and Josh Caldwell added 10 points and had seven rebounds for the Black Knights (11-8, 5-2 Patriot League), Stacy Beckton Jr. had 15 points for the Eagles (5-11, 1-3). Elijah Stephens scored 13 and Connor Nelson 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
